<span id="freeTextContainer13809686384623911744">My only recommendation (re: this edition at least)--don&apos;t read the foreword or preface until AFTER reading the text. <br/><br/>Both seem designed to obscure &amp; show off to other academics, as opposed to inform, unlike Fanon&apos;s writing itself.<br/><br/>This book is a very calm, determined &amp; clarifying analysis and that I will chew on for a long long time.<br/><br/>It&apos;s not as dated as it &quot;should&quot; be so it&apos;s as relevant as ever.</span>
  <span id="freeText13809686384623911744" style="display:none">My only recommendation (re: this edition at least)--don't read the foreword or preface until AFTER reading the text. <br /><br />Both seem designed to obscure &amp; show off to other academics, as opposed to inform, unlike Fanon's writing itself.<br /><br />This book is a very calm, determined &amp; clarifying analysis and that I will chew on for a long long time.<br /><br />It's not as dated as it "should" be so it's as relevant as ever.</span>
