<span id="freeTextContainer2299201661620721994">Must-read for those interested in the effects of colonialism &amp; skeptical about the inevitability of violent rebellion. May not convince you of the necessity of violence, but will explain a few things about the psychology of colonialist occupation. it&apos;s not a perfect book - it&apos;s full of bitterness and vitriol, but some of its insights are astounding.</span>
