<div id="review_3385117069" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3385117069" />
    <a title="Erik" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/15103969-erik"><img alt="Erik" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1627042042p2/15103969.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3385117069?book_show_action=true">Jun 12, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Erik" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Erik" href="/user/show/15103969-erik">Erik</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/15103969-erik?shelf=poc-authored">poc-authored</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3385117069" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7142126866028991234">A masterpiece in its imagination, scholarship, and theory, Frantz Fanon&apos;s &quot;The Wretched of the Earth&quot; lays the groundwork for much of racial theory that would follow.<br/><br/>In succinct yet thorough chapters Fanon lays out the ways in which a colonized people can gain its independence from Europe and embark on a journey to independence, avoiding landmines on the way. And in each step, Fanon&apos;s radical method is simple: understand that the masses hold the keys to the kingdom, pre-colonial history should b</span>
  <span id="freeText7142126866028991234" style="display:none">A masterpiece in its imagination, scholarship, and theory, Frantz Fanon's "The Wretched of the Earth" lays the groundwork for much of racial theory that would follow.<br /><br />In succinct yet thorough chapters Fanon lays out the ways in which a colonized people can gain its independence from Europe and embark on a journey to independence, avoiding landmines on the way. And in each step, Fanon's radical method is simple: understand that the masses hold the keys to the kingdom, pre-colonial history should be recognized but not reified, and national culture can encourage political education and help combat the pseudo-bourgeoisie and nationalism that may crop up in the newly independent state.<br /><br />The last chapter, on psychoanalysis and the colonial subject, is out of place, but the rest of the book is so remarkable that it earned 5 stars despite the mistake of including it. In a time where racial ideas are being challenged, brought into the global mindset, and discussed openly, Fanon's book reminds of the importance of saying "no" to concessions and demanding the radical changes that will ensure a better society for all.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7142126866028991234" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review3385117069">
  <td colspan="2">
    <div class="updateActionLinks">
        <a class="right flag" rel="nofollow" id="flag_link3385117069" title="Flag this review as inappropriate." href="/flagged/new?resource_id=3385117069&amp;resource_type=Review&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F66933.The_Wretched_of_the_Earth">flag</a>





      <span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_review_3385117069'><a id="like_count_review_3385117069" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/3385117069?resource_type=Review"><span class="likesCount">8 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it gr-button gr-button--small" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F66933.The_Wretched_of_the_Earth">Like</a></span>
